
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gtk-update-icon-cache` baraye dorost kardan (create) ya update kardan cache-haye icon baraye theme-haye GTK estefade mishavad. Yani baraye inke icon-ha be tore dorost dar barname-ha namayesh dade shavand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gtk-update-icon-cache --force`  --> 🔄 Majboor mikonad cache ra update konad, hata age taghirati ehsas nashavad.
    🔹 `gtk-update-icon-cache --ignore-errors`  --> ⚠️ Agar khataei dar hengam dorost kardan cache rokh bedahad, az an gozashteh va edame midahad.
    🔹 `gtk-update-icon-cache --quiet`  --> 🤫 Hich payami dar terminal namayesh nemidahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gtk-update-icon-cache /usr/share/icons/hicolor

    🔹 Icon cache ra baraye theme "hicolor" update mikonad.

    $ sudo gtk-update-icon-cache --force /usr/share/icons/mytheme

    🔹 Icon cache ra baraye theme "mytheme" ba majbur kardan update mikonad (ba dastresi root).

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gtk-update-icon-cache --quiet /usr/share/icons/mytheme

    🔹 Icon cache ra baraye theme "mytheme" update mikonad va hich payami namayesh nemidahad. In baraye script-ha mofid ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gtk-update-icon-cache` command is used to create or update the icon cache for GTK themes. This ensures that icons are displayed correctly in applications.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gtk-update-icon-cache --force`  --> 🔄 Forces the cache to be updated, even if no changes are detected.
    🔹 `gtk-update-icon-cache --ignore-errors`  --> ⚠️ Ignores errors that occur during cache creation and continues.
    🔹 `gtk-update-icon-cache --quiet`  --> 🤫 Suppresses all output messages to the terminal.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gtk-update-icon-cache /usr/share/icons/hicolor

    🔹 Updates the icon cache for the "hicolor" theme.

    $ sudo gtk-update-icon-cache --force /usr/share/icons/mytheme

    🔹 Forces the icon cache to be updated for the "mytheme" theme (using root privileges).

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gtk-update-icon-cache --quiet /usr/share/icons/mytheme

    🔹 Updates the icon cache for the "mytheme" theme without displaying any output. This is useful for scripts.
